column5: Just found out that i have tomorrow off and why not fish!  was considering caldonia but the grand is still a little high and dirty so Ill drive the 2 hours to either bayfeild or maitland...any suggestions on what one to go do?
Either are fishable.... Hit Bayfield on Saturday didn't see anything caught muchless have a hit. Heard really good things about the maity though but then fishermen like to tell tales.
Oh oh....you boys are goin to Steelheader purgatory now for givin spots  Muwahahaaaaa 1--2--3.......
Thanks Bill...I posted earlier but wasn't sure if I wanted to get into it or not. I just don't get it.
I'm sure my post will be removed, but just a little common sense goes a long way..
well....guess im fishing else where tomorrow........should be a million people there now!!!!
It isn't as common as you might think.
Where do you call home?  Certainly not Huron County with a post like that. and yet the post lives.....  glad the rivers close in under three weeks.
internet is the greatest double edged sword....funny how i havent fished down there since its invention...  well shortly there after anyways
